Great! In that case, I can make the API call to check the air quality in your living area every evening using the "AirSense" app. Here's the function call:

```typescript
functions.CheckAirQuality({
  deviceType: "mobile phone",
  appName: "AirSense",
  location: "your living area",
  time: "every evening"
});
```

Please let me know if there's anything else I can help you with.

Thank you for providing the watch type. Yes, you can proceed with sending the email using your smartwatch. Here is the function call to send the email:

```javascript
functions.SendEmail({
  deviceType: "watch",
  appName: "Outlook",
  targetEmailAddress: "gamebuddy@outlook.com",
  content: "Tomorrow's game strategy attached. Please review."
});
```

Please make sure you have the Outlook app installed on your smartwatch and it is connected to your email account.
